OL,3,CJersey headteachers unanimously vote
OL,4,Cagainst introducing bilingual schools
OL,6,FNevertheless, a survey sent to all
OL,7,Fprimary school headteachers in Jersey
OL,8,Frevealed that none of the 21
OL,9,Frespondents believe they should
OL,10,Fconvert their primary school or three
OL,11,FGovernment of Jersey primary schools,
OL,12,Fto an English-French bilingual school.
OL,14,F14 schools say none of their current
OL,15,Fteachers are fluent in French or have
OL,16,Fthe ability to plan, teach and monitor
OL,17,Fchildren's progress across all
OL,18,Fsubjects on the Jersey Curriculum in
OL,19,Fboth French and English.
