OL,3,CJersey headteachers unanimously vote
OL,4,Cagainst introducing bilingual schools
OL,6,FWhilst six schools voted they had one
OL,7,Fteacher viable and only one school
OL,8,Fsaid they had two.
OL,10,FThe report also revealed teachers'
OL,11,Fcomments, which disclosed that the
OL,12,Fteachers unanimously disagreed with
OL,13,Fthe proposition.
OL,15,FOne headteacher says: "This should be
OL,16,Fa non-starter. There are many greater,
OL,17,Fmore pressing needs to be addressed in
OL,18,Fschools."
