OL,3,CJersey headteachers unanimously vote
OL,4,Cagainst introducing bilingual schools
OL,6,FOne response also questions why the
OL,7,Fproposition is specifically for a
OL,8,FFrench school: "Jersey is a multi-
OL,9,Flingual island.
OL,11,F"The second and third languages of the
OL,12,Fisland are not French, but Portuguese
OL,13,Fand Polish.
OL,15,F"If we were to offer bilingual
OL,16,Fprovision, it ought to be in these
OL,17,Flanguages."
